text: After seeing the process and the thoughts behind every single song on this album, I have a feeling that I'm going to have a special connection to each song in a different way. I also love how Taeyong put an optimistic message at the end of every one of his song explanations as a way to tell people that you can have hardships and go through dark times but there is always a light on the flip side of that darkness. Albums that have time and dedication put into them make me respect artists even more than I did before. The realness of the songs is going to create such an amazing collection of songs that I can't wait to listen to.

text:
I'm probably late now but I'm totally In love with this film. I like it much better than the usual high end set & probs promo videos.
This album is the most hand on the most personal gift we received from him & it shows how Taeyong is his own league and is above  the limitation of the idol title but a very all rounder perfect artist. They way every song is a story on itself and a meaningful sentimental one at that. I cried when he mentioned Ruby & Back to the past & the art portray of his family hugging him was so warming and devastating for me at the same time considering everything he went through.
I'm more than proud with how far he's come , his existence on its own is truly a gift & blessing.
You deserve to have the best of this world & I hope you continue making music with a full wide green forest of a mind & heart.
I love you so much.

author: @fenchortu
text:
Taeyong is such a bright force. watching him talk about his songs and his creative process in this documentary-like video brought me a wave of serenity traced with anticipation. I like the way he looks at the world, wide-eyed in wonder and with pure honesty. I'm really looking forward to his album, especially the song Ruby, cause its description has already teared me up. also 404 file not found, I just find it fascinating how honest he always seems, genuine and real, while it's probably much easier to hide as much of yourself as you can when you're under constant attention and inspection. And it was sad when he said "if I wasn't an idol and had a normal life, I'd be so happy and bubbly just strolling in this weather like that." This is the kind of payoff that is inevitable and longing for it is bittersweet(of course in an ideal world fame wouldn't have to operate that way but this is far from an ideal world).
I can't wait to listen to Shalala and watch the amazing animations made for each track.

author: @biasandbinge
text: First thing first, I was watching it with *precise concentration* for some reason. Let me *take a breath* and you guys should also *take a moment to form right words* in your mind to appreciate *the man* who been a *constant pillar* in this legacy that was created. I might end up writing down a whole essay at this moment, but I don't have and would never have the eyes for *so many details* that he has pointed out and seen. It's an overwhelming roller-coaster must be, from beginning to at this point with greatness with flaws (believe me you are perfect TY!!!), but the keen eyes that he has for fragments and stories is worthy of the tale we tell to generation. As if very being, every emotion has taken place in here, the way we got to *visualize without effort* (At one point I was sure that we are going to get 7 M/V for Godsâ€™ sake!!) definitely impressive beyond my words. Think of being a man who just put on sentence and itâ€™s a testament to follow! The way he connect with beings, place, memories (I could never!) is a *clear evidence* that he never lied to what he felt, what he said, what he dreamed. Now that I think of it, few of his *tattoos also bought into words* (I mean how much he meant what he meant so deeply!!!). I am not going to talk about the low-key teaser of every song through instrumental, but I can say they depict *THE LEE TAEYONG* very smoothly sharply verifying the different side he has (God made TY and gave him the key to our hearts!!!). Gotta tell about the photos that been *kxllxng me all the past week* (Dude knows what is style!!!). *To the people behind all the greatness of TY from the journeysâ€™ beginning to until now and to the people who are behind every portion of this album must give my utmost respect to them who made this possible for him.* I was never so very excited for a solo debut in all my life, now that I am here, got to see the creation of something extraordinary, something beautiful and very little something of *THE LEE TAEYONG, the leader of NCT!!!* (Crying in the corner, writing my thought leaving my exam study tomorrow, but itâ€™s worth it!)
